The '''HelmKit''' is the [[Tho'ra Clan]]'s standard wearable mounting platform for head-worn operational gear. It is, literally, a ''kit for the helm'': a modular helmet-and-headset frame carrying standardized rails, optical bays, power, and data interfaces, into which any combination of [[Psi-Tech]], [[Star Seer]] HUD, [[NavCom]] HUD, sensor packs, and comms modules can be installed. The HelmKit is the operator-side foundation of the Clan's field stack — its job is not to ''do'' anything specific, it is to ''carry'' the things that do, and to keep the operator safe while they do.

This page covers the HelmKit as a product line. For the deeper engineering — bus, power budget, dual-MCU safety architecture, watchdogs, thermal limits — see [[HelmKit Architecture]].

{{Defensive-publication}}

== Overview ==

The HelmKit is built around four design commitments:

* '''Modular.''' Every functional component (display, sensor pack, [[Psi Stabilizer]], [[Psi Harmonizer]], [[Psi Defender]], audio, lighting) attaches via a standardized rail and bay system. The frame survives generational upgrades of its modules.
* '''Safety-architected.''' From Mk1 onward, every active module passes through a supervisory MCU enforcing RF-power, thermal, and battery-current limits. See [[HelmKit Architecture]] §Safety.
* '''Cosplay-compatible by construction.''' The Mk0 shell is intentionally identical in external form to Mk1+ functional units. Public visibility doubles as recruitment signal and brand carrier; it also lets an operator wear functional gear in public without disclosing capability.
* '''Operator-configurable.''' Each [[Tho'ra Clan|Tho'ra]] builds their own loadout for the role they walk into. Recruit, pilot, command, analyst, and civilian-cosplay configurations are documented but not enforced.

== Theoretical Basis ==

The HelmKit itself is mechanical and electrical engineering — it makes no psionic claim. What it ''carries'' does, and those claims are tagged on the respective module pages. Three working assumptions structure the platform:

* {{Psi-claim
| status = PROVISIONAL
| cites = [[Geomagnetic Sensitivity in Humans]]
| methods = Multiple converging studies; replication still in progress.
| falsifier = Pre-registered, multi-site replication returning a null result (Bayes factor &le; 1/3).
| confidence = medium
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} Head-mounted sensors are useful because the head is the most stable, most sensor-rich, and most cognitively-coupled mount point on the body. Helmet-borne magnetometers, IMUs, EEG, and PPG are standard in research-grade neuroinstrumentation.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = TESTABLE
| cites = [[Resonant Neurobiology]], [[Heart Rate Variability and Psi]]
| methods = Concrete protocol defined; replication not yet attempted.
| falsifier = A blinded study following the proposed protocol returning a null result at p < 0.01.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} A head-mounted, sensor-coupled, RF-capable platform is the right substrate for testing whether closed-loop biofeedback can stabilize the operator under high-stress conditions. This is a falsifiable engineering claim, not a psionic one.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = SPECULATIVE
| cites = [[Scalar Electromagnetic Waves]], [[Psi Field]]
| methods = Theoretical; not yet operationalised into a testable protocol.
| falsifier = Quantitative prediction shown to conflict with established physics or biology.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} ''If'' a [[Psi Field]] exists as a field-theoretic quantity, the HelmKit's near-field RF bays and shielded compartments are the correct platform for emitting, detecting, and shaping it. The HelmKit does not depend on this claim being true — its non-psionic functions stand on their own.

== Subsystems and BOM ==

=== Reference module bays ===

* '''Optical bay (L / R / center)''' — [[Star Seer]] HUD, [[NavCom]] HUD, low-light optic, IR overlay.
* '''Sensor pack''' — magnetometer, electrostatic probe, barometric, IMU, ambient EM.
* '''Psi bay''' — [[Psi Stabilizer]], [[Psi Harmonizer]], [[Psi Defender]], or an integrated triad module.
* '''Comms''' — [[NavCom]] radio, encrypted PTT, bone-conduction audio.
* '''Compute''' — on-helm SoC, supervisory MCU, battery, PMIC.
* '''Cosmetic / brand layer''' — personal heraldry, faction insignia, RGB.

