== Build Notes ==

* '''Frame.''' Print at 0.2 mm layer, 3 walls, 30 % gyroid. Brass heat-set inserts on every load-bearing screw. Avoid PLA in cabin temperatures > 50 °C — switch to PETG or ASA.
* '''Mass budget.''' Mk0 ≤ 600 g. Mk1 ≤ 850 g. Anything over 1 kg becomes a neck-strain issue inside an hour.
* '''Cable routing.''' All cables route through the back-of-helm channel into a single connector pod above the C7 vertebra. Detach point lives in the breakaway lanyard; no cable runs across the throat.
* '''Module IDs.''' Every bay reads a 1-byte identity from the module's I²C address 0x00 register on insert. Unknown modules are powered to 3.3 V signalling only — no rails — until the operator confirms.

== Safety and Ethics ==

The HelmKit's safety envelope is enforced by the supervisory MCU-B documented in [[HelmKit Architecture]]:

* RF emitter aggregate power capped at the lesser of {ICNIRP basic restriction at near-field separation 1 cm} or {per-module declared maximum} − 6 dB headroom.
* Thermal sensors at psi-bay, optical bay, and battery; any reading > 50 °C trips the bay; > 60 °C trips the whole helm.
* Battery cell-level fuse + reverse-polarity FET + per-rail current sense.
* Hard kill: a single breakaway pull at the lanyard severs the upstream PMIC enable.

Ethics: a HelmKit must never act on a third party. All emitters are near-field, directed at the wearer. The [[Psi Defender]] is shield, not sword. The [[Psi Harmonizer]] interlocks to the wearer's own [[natal chart]] only — never another person's. See [[Tho'ra Mission Doctrine]].

