== Failure Modes and Mitigations ==

* '''Battery thermal runaway.''' → Cell-level fuse, per-rail current sense, MCU-B watchdog. Worst case: hard-kill lanyard.
* '''Module misidentification.''' → 1-byte identity probe at 3.3 V signalling only before rail power; operator confirmation for unknown IDs.
* '''Operator fatigue / neck strain.''' → Mass cap 850 g Mk1; reset reminders every 90 minutes.
* '''Cable snag.''' → All routing internal; single external lanyard with breakaway.
* '''RF emitter stuck-on.''' → MCU-B independently times every emit cycle; hard-cut on watchdog miss.
* '''Cosmetic-only Mk0 mistaken for active.''' → Mk0 frames carry an internal visible-light-only marker; Mk1+ require key-on auth.

